<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">skyh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hi All,<P>I recently tried to solo an *EASY* green conning griffawn in NK. I am level 19, well armed and armored (PGT and Langseax, crafted boots, bracer, gloves, STR 130, AGi 95, DEX 105, STA 107), my weapon skills pretty well maxxed.<P>Since I had SOW, I kited it with a bow (16 dmg oak 2-cam) for a while, then melee'd it. Despite conning easy green, despite my being well-equipped for my level, it totally kicked my butt. In the end only my SOW saved me, as I had to run for the guards (about 1.5 bubbles left, griffawn at about 40%).<P>A friendly druid intervened at that point, buffing and healing me and occasionally nuking the griffawn. Even so, I just barely managed to kill it with less than a bubble of health left.<P>Do griffawns routinely con much lower than their actual level, is this a bug in EQ's con system, or just a nasty trick Verant likes to play on warriors?<P>Thanks,<P>------------------<BR>Iuediwen, Lvl 10 High Elf Magician<BR>Horalf, Lvl 19 Dwarven Warrior <BR>Skywilde, Lvl 7 High Elf Enchanter</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Nope Griffs are totally out of whack from their con. As a warrior you cant really trust con anyway but Griffs are about the worst offenders. The other type of mob that cons way off are named mobs.  Just because they are bleu or green to you does not mean you dont have to fear a named mob.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warduh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">LOL u are starting to get to that point where u will not be able to Solo nothing That all it is LOL <P>------------------<BR>WARDUH<BR>OGRE WARROIR<BR>ME SMASH ME BASH <BR>ME KILL ALL</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">All griffins fall into that category of mobs that are far harder than what they con.  The main reason is that they hit way too hard for their level.<P>And you're lucky you lived.  I remember a light green griffawn spanking my hiney when i was 23!!<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>45 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">skyh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"> <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/frown.gif">  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/frown.gif">  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/frown.gif"><BR><P>------------------<BR>Iuediwen, Lvl 10 High Elf Magician<BR>Horalf, Lvl 19 Dwarven Warrior <BR>Skywilde, Lvl 7 High Elf Enchanter</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Viacain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Oh... it's not that bad... I still regularly solo.... and ask Rautha, she was my solo idol for a while before she became a group-monkey  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR><B>Geok</B> 30th lvl Troll Warrior on Brell <I>DELETED</I><BR><B>Geok</B> 34th lvl Troll Warrior on Brell <I>RESSURECTED!</I><BR><B>????</B> 10th lvl Twinky Wizard Side Project for Prime Time Crowding</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Viacain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">To clarify:<P>You have to choose your battles much more carefully as you rise in levels as a warrior...<BR>The Griffawns are just another valuable lesson, be glad you were able to learn it without a death!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">MGonly1</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I believe the con is partly because I have realized that they have pretty low resists to most spells.  I conned them black to our group (I was the Shaman), and nobody could melee the bastages  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/frown.gif">  However they took full damage on everybodies spells.  I think that is the justification behind the con.  I don't agree with it mind you, I think they should have the con be effected by your class as well as level.  Just something I noticed about Griffawns, I have no knowledge of the Griffiennes, or Griffons yet though.<P>Warell<BR>Wood Elf Warrior 10 cycles on Norrath<P>Prodorf Spiritforge<BR>Barbarian Shaman 24 cycles on Norrath</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>Yeah, as a warrior you'll quickly learn not to trust a con.  I think it was around 30th level that I even had a chance at soloing Dorn (who cons around 16th).  He has the HP of a 16th level mob, but dodges and parries like a 25th level one, making him a hard target for a tank.  Grifs have the HP of their con, but dish out more damage than they should.<P>In short, be careful of Griffs, and be careful of named mobs.  (And be *really* careful of named Griffs... Grimfeather, holy *$&#^!!).<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFF